Scope of the Reference Implementation

This reference implementation includes the demo, scripts, outputs, validation traces, and supporting artifacts provided in this release.

SSUM-Time defines a deterministic structural time reconstruction architecture based on alignment between multiple deterministic cycles.

The architecture establishes the following conceptual model:

t_est_next = t_est + f(observed_phase − expected_phase)

Where:

t_est — internal temporal estimate

observed_phase — observed structural cycle phase

expected_phase — predicted phase from the structural model

f() — bounded structural correction function

The reference implementation demonstrates:

• structural cycle alignment for time reconstruction
• deterministic correction of internal time estimates
• reliability-aware governance states
• graceful degradation under partial cycle loss
• safety abstention when structural alignment cannot be trusted
• persistence of temporal trajectory through continuity state (auto-captured in the reference demo)

The reference implementation is provided to demonstrate architectural feasibility of structural time reconstruction.


Conformance

An implementation is considered compatible with the SSUM-Time reference architecture if it preserves the core structural principles demonstrated by the implementation, including:

• deterministic structural correction behavior
• structural phase alignment evaluation
• bounded correction updates
• explicit governance states controlling solver behavior
• deterministic recovery behavior under replay conditions

Independent implementations are permitted and encouraged.


