Closing Statement

SSUM-Time is published to explore the possibility that temporal continuity can be reconstructed through deterministic structural alignment of cycles.

The project is released openly to encourage independent research, validation, and implementation of structural time reconstruction architectures.

Timekeeping, long governed by oscillators, may also be understood as a structural inference process.

SSUM-Time is offered as a reference architecture for that exploration.
